# jobhound_core Development Guidelines

Spec-driven workflow via `.specify` and `/speckit.*` commands. Update this file when plans change (or run the Specify update script when wired).

## Active Technologies

- Go 1.24 — standard library first; `net/http` / `html` / `encoding/json` for Tier-1 API and static fetchers
- `github.com/PuerkitoBio/goquery` for HTML sources (Tier 2)
- `github.com/go-rod/rod` + session cookies file for LinkedIn (Tier 3)
- PostgreSQL + GORM + migrations — jobs, history, profile, dedup
- Temporal — workflows/activities for manual runs and scheduled events
- Claude API for scoring; Telegram Bot API for delivery
- Local: Docker Compose (Postgres + Temporal); production: GCP (see `specs/000-epic-overview`)

## Project Structure

```text
cmd/agent/              # wiring: compose app.Pipeline from adapters
config/
internal/domain/        # Job, ScoredJob, pure types
internal/ports/         # Collector, Filter, Scorer, Dedup, Notifier, SessionProvider
internal/app/           # orchestration only (e.g. Pipeline.Run); no service→service
internal/adapters/      # noop + future source-specific collectors, Telegram, GORM repos
```

**Layers**: handlers / `cmd` → `app` (orchestration) → `ports` (interfaces). Domain services (when added) take **repository ports only**, not other services, to avoid import cycles. Cross-cutting composition stays in `cmd` or `app`.

## Commands

- `make build` — compile `./cmd/agent` to `bin/agent`
- `make run` — build and run agent
- `make test` — `go test ./...`
- `make fmt` / `make vet` / `make tidy`

## Code Style

- Go 1.24 conventions; boundary interfaces live in `internal/ports`; implementations under `internal/adapters` or `internal/<feature>/storage`
- No secrets or real `.env` in git — see `make help` for documented env variable names
- Table-driven tests where behavior branches; keep `main` thin

